	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=64677><span id=Sage>xaanru</span></a><br><b><span id=Sage>Sage</span></b><br><span id=notbold>2023 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default [2.10]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Ok, look at this cloak this way. Just for a moment, ignore the -10 to save poison and disease, and look at 5ac, 10 mana, 10hp. 5 ac is not bad for a caster back item, and 10 mana is quite a bit for a lower level character, up to maybe 20, if untwinked, 10 hp is extra mana thru cannibalize. I would see this item as one that you might switch out when fighting certain mobs. It only weighs .5, so no biggy to carry in the backpack, and when not fighting mobs with disease or poison attacks, it's actually a pretty nice caster item. Further, even with poison or disease based mobs, it they only have a melee proc type attack, then you're still in good shape, as the pet should keep it off of you. </p>&nbsp;<br></td></td></tr>
